<p>Integration Language Course "German as a second language" according to the Immigration Act (Zuwanderungsgesetz)</p>
<p>Basic courses (Basic level A1)<b>, </b>Advanced classes level A2 and B1<b>: </b>25 lessons per week</p>
<div class="page-header">
<h2>Who are the Integration courses meant for?</h2>
</div>
<p>This course is meant for foreigners, and migrants who have permission to live in Germany for an extended period of time (at least 2 years).</p>
<div class="page-header">
<h2>What is an Integration Course?</h2>
</div>
<p>All of our integration courses include: Intensive language instruction with a total of 600 classroom hours consisting of 45 minute lessons and an orientation course with a total of 60 lessons.</p>
<p>The language course is divided into a 300 hour basic course and a 300 hour intermediate course. Upon completion of this course particiants are qualified to take the German <b>Cercification </b>Test which is recognized throughout Germany as well as the rest of Europe as proof of having knowledge of the German language at the intermediate level.<p>
</div>
